cs.NE, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.AI 

This paper is about a self-adaptive version of an evolutionary algorithm, which is a common technique in the field of neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also contributes new tools for the analysis of drift processes, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper includes a runtime analysis, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
